T=8 keV diffuse emission are equally unsatisfying. We are\nleft to conclude that either the diffuse emission is heated by an unanticipated\nsource of energy, or that a population of faint (< 10^31 erg/s), hard X-ray\nsources that are a factor of 10 more numerous than CVs remains to be\ndiscovered. (Abridged)\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 3 Feb 2004 23:11:07 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 1 Jun 2004 19:50:35 GMT"}],"update_date":"2008-11-26"}
