od to\nsimulate the properties of $\\gamma$-ray pulsars in our galaxy. We find that\nthis new outer gap model predicts many more weak $\\gamma$-ray pulsars. For all\nsimulated $\\gamma$-ray pulsars with self-sustained outer gaps, $\\gamma$-ray\nluminosity $L_{\\gamma}$ satisfies $L_{\\gamma}\\propto L^{\\delta}_{sd}$; where\nthe value of $\\delta$ depends on the ensitivity of the $\\gamma$-ray detector.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 4 Feb 2004 02:27:34 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-10"}
